HEADWORD: Hypermetrical
<hw>Hy`per*met"ric*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a
redundant syllable; exceeding the common measure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hypermetrical verse</b></col> <fld>(Gr. & Lat.
Pros.)</fld>, <cd>a verse which contains a syllable more than the
ordinary measure.</cd></cs></p>

